aah","tag-fiqh","tag-good-deeds-hasanat","tag-imam-abu-hanifa","tag-imam-ahmad-ibn-hanbal","tag-imam-ash-shafiee","tag-imam-malik","tag-manners-adab","tag-mosques-masjid","tag-obligations-faraid","tag-prayer-al-salat","tag-virtue-al-fadail"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-48U","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15928,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37364,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/11\/dhikr-after-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15928,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Dhikr: Remembering Allah loudly or softly after prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The people would raise their voices in remembrance as they left the obligatory prayers in the time of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. Ibn Abbas said, \u201cI used to know when they were leaving as I heard them.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 841, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11562,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/22\/walking-salat-waiting-imam\/","url_meta":{"origin":15928,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Masjid: Reward for walking to prayer, waiting for Imam","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 22, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Musa reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe people with the greatest reward are those who walk the furthest, then the next furthest. Those who wait to pray with the Imam have a greater reward than those who pray alone and then sleep.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28905,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/taraweeh-ramadan-imam-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15928,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Tarawih: Reward for praying with the Imam until he finishes","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Dharr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, whoever stands for prayer in Ramadan with the Imam until he is finished, it will be recorded as if he prayed the entire night.\u201d Imam al-Tirmidhi commented, \u201cThe scholars differed over the night prayer in\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14904,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/10\/suhur-recite-fifty-ayat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15928,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Suhur: Prolonging pre-fasting meal before Fajr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 10, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Thabit reported: We ate the pre-fasting meal\u00a0with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and then we stood for prayer. It was asked, \u201cHow long was it between the two calls to prayer?\u201d Zayd said, \u201cIt was time enough to recite fifty verses from the Quran.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33168,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/11\/imam-rabbana-lakal-hamd\/","url_meta":{"origin":15928,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Salat: What to say when Imam rises in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the Imam says, \u2018Allah heard those who praise him,\u2019 then say, \u2018Our Lord, for you is praise.\u2019 If one\u2019s statement coincides with the statement of the angels, his previous sins will be forgiven.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_li